                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                <date>27<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> May 1862</date>.</p>\n            <p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir—</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">The commencement of the College<lb/> recess gives me leisure to\n                attend some what to<lb/> correspondence too much neglected. I have a<lb/> very\n                respectable pile of letters before me of rather<lb/> antique date which testify and\n                declare that I have<lb/> either been lazy these last few months, or my time<lb/> has\n                been much occupied. I rather incline to the<lb/> latter supposition and I hope you\n                will also—at<lb/> least I have had the wish to write you ere this.<lb/> With the\n                resolution of years I find I have new<lb/> duties and new claims on my time. My\n                    <add>בכור</add><lb/> must be examined occasionally to see how he<lb/> “gets on”\n                at school where he learns English<lb/> grammar, arithmetic, French &amp;c and as I\n                am<lb/> his Hebrew pedagogue at home, the young<lb/> gentleman (now <add>?</add> in\n                his ninth year),<lb/> takes up a little of my time. The application<lb/> of this\n                long interesting <add>הקדמה</add> I leave to yourself.<lb/> I have commenced, but\n                not finished the Biography<lb/> of my late revered father <add>ע\"ה</add> to which\n                you</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p37h1f675/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
