                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>refer in your last. I have before written you that<lb/> I was asked for it elsewhere;\n                though I should<lb/> be very pleased to see it in the Occident, and<lb/> shall\n                certainly send you a copy duly authenticated<lb/> as you request. You are not, you\n                write, a close<lb/> reader of the Jewish publications—neither am I.<lb/> I give you,\n                as you requested me, credit for<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr J. H. J's</persName> $3— Please inform me how our<lb/> account stands.\n                I regret to say I am not quite<lb/> sure as to the Calendars I sent you.\n                Besides<lb/> the dozen sent you per <persName>Miss S. J.</persName> (<date>21 May\n                    '61</date>)<lb/> you had “ I reckon” another dozen. Please<lb/> let me know how\n                the matter really is, as<lb/> though I made an entry some where, I cannot<lb/>\n                remember where just now.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">As items of news (if such indeed<lb/> they be to you) I might\n                mention that our<lb/> synagogue was reopened for the late holy days<lb/> after\n                having been thoroughly renovated<lb/> internally. The cong. have been much<lb/>\n                indebted to the pious zeal of <persName>Mrs Henry Benjamin</persName></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p37h1f675/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
